'''Bodhiraja Buddhist Society''' is a [[Theravada]] organisation in [[Singapore]]. The present premises are located at [[Geylang]], [[Singapore]].

==Overview==

'''Bodhiraja Buddhist Society''' was founded as a [[theravada]] Buddhist organisation in Singapore by Ven Dr [[Omalpe Sobhita Thero]]. It is related with the [http://www.bodhirajafoundation.org Sri Bodhiraja Foundation] in [[Sri Lanka]] which participated in the reconstruction and relief efforts accruing from the [[tsunami]] victims in [[Hambantota]]<ref>{{cite news|last1=Tan|first1=Suyin|title=Sri Lanka: More houses of love as project Meth Sevana starts second phase|url=http://reliefweb.int/report/sri-lanka/sri-lanka-more-houses-love-project-meth-sevana-starts-second-phase|accessdate=30 September 2014|agency=Singapore Red Cross|publisher=ReliefWeb}}</ref> and also towards the closure of the [[Sri Lankan Civil War]].<ref>{{cite journal|title=Our Aid|journal=Big Grin Organics|url=http://biggrinorganics.blogspot.sg/2009/04/our-aid.html|accessdate=30 September 2014}}</ref> The center conducts a variety of buddhist services and activities on a weekly basis.<ref>{{cite journal|title=2006 April Activities|journal=For You Information|issue=204|accessdate=9 September 2014}}</ref>

